article.headline: Stetson 63, North Florida 60, OT
article.story: JACKSONVILLE, Fla. (AP) -- Garfield Blair scored five of his team-high 14 points in overtime as Stetson held off North Florida 63-60 Thursday. The Hatters (7-12, 3-5 Atlantic Sun Conference) struggled from the floor during regulation but found their shooting touch in overtime. Stetson made five consecutive free throws to take a six-point lead with 51 seconds left in overtime. North Florida (2-16, 0-8) managed to cut the lead to three with six seconds remaining on a Jonson Yousefzadeh 3-point shot, but a 3-pointer from Aaron Caruthers was short. North Florida guard Chris Timberlake tied the game at the end of regulation with a driving layup that cleared the net at the buzzer. Timberlake finished with 17 points. He also had eight assists and seven rebounds. The two teams traded leads through much of the game as Stetson struggled to attack North Florida's zone defense. Stetson shot close to 37 percent from the floor in the game. North Florida missed its one attempted 3-point shot, but the team made half of shots its from inside the arc in the first half.
